<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-fl9aRkVjGCfSXPW6XWk3gQ" name=",_5bEIEKZKEeCmzNtTCfivQw" guid="-fl9aRkVjGCfSXPW6XWk3gQ" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    ISO 26262, volume 8, clause 9 defines the guidance for generic aspects of verification planning which should be followed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    In order to detect systematic faults within the implementation of system design during the hardware-software&#xD;
    integration various test methods must be selected that cover a variety of aspects of test and verification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The selection of the application&amp;nbsp;feasible methods are detailed in the step section.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>The test planning must include the verification of the on-board communication network and its interaction with the on board&#xD;
power supply.</keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_6r3tAKZoEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Selection of  methods for the correctness of implementation of functional safety requirements" guid="_6r3tAKZoEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;To ensure the correctness of implementation of functional safety requirements, all the following types of test&#xD;
    are highly recommended at all ASIL levels:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Requirements-based test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Fault injection test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Long term test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        User test under real life conditions&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Requirements based testing is used to test against functional and non-functional (quality of service) requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Fault injection test uses special means to introduce faults into the item. This can be done within the item via a&#xD;
    special test interface or specially prepared elements or communication devices. The method is often used to improve the&#xD;
    test coverage of the safety requirements, because during normal operation safety mechanisms are not invoked&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
    A long term test and a user test under real-life conditions are similar to tests derived from field experience but use&#xD;
    a larger sample size, normal users as testers, and are not bound to prior specified test scenarios, but performed under&#xD;
    real-life conditions during everyday life.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
    This summary is based upon &quot;Table 14 Correctness of implementation of functional safety requirements&quot;, located in ISO&#xD;
    26262, volume 4, clause 8.4.4.3.1.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_MeUa8KZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Selection of  methods for the correctness of functional performance, accuracy and timing of safety mechanisms" guid="_MeUa8KZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To ensure the&amp;nbsp;correctness of functional performance, accuracy and timing of safety mechanisms, the following types&#xD;
    of test are recommended at ASIL A or B, and highly recommended at ASIL C and D:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Performance test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Long term test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        User test under real-life conditions&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Performance testing is used to verify the perfomance of the item's safety mechanisms.&amp;nbsp;These tests cover aspects&#xD;
    such as fault tolerant time intervals and vehicle controllability in the presence of faults.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Long term and user test under real life conditions, use a large sample size with normal users as testers. The users are&#xD;
    not bound to pre determined test scenarios, but the tests are carried out during normal real-life conditions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please refer to &quot;&lt;a id=&quot;_Toc229203836&quot; name=&quot;_Toc229203836&quot;>Table15-Correctness of functional performance, accuracy and&#xD;
    timing of safety mechanisms&quot;,&amp;nbsp;located in&amp;nbsp;ISO 26262, volume 4, clause 8.4.4.3.3 for the full&#xD;
    details.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/a>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_U3gTcKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Selection of  methods for the consistency and correctness of implementation of external interfaces" guid="_U3gTcKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Please refer to &quot;Table 16-Consistency and correctness of implementation of external interfaces&quot;, located at ISO 26262,&#xD;
    volume&amp;nbsp;4, clause 8.4.4.3.3 to&amp;nbsp;find the recommendations regarding testing of interfaces. In summary the tests&#xD;
    covered are the following:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Test if external interfaces&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Test of interaction/communication&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Both types of tests are recommended at ASIL B and highly recommended at ASILs C or D.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Testing of external interfaces at the vehicle level is an examination of the interfaces of the vehicle for&#xD;
    compatibility, These tests are done statically (by validating value ranges, ratings or geometries)&amp;nbsp; and&#xD;
    dynamically (during operation of the whole vehicle).&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    Communication and interactions tests are carried out on the vehicle at runtime and check the communication between&#xD;
    systems against the functional and non functional requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_dy0ooKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Selection of  methods for the effectiveness and failure coverage of safety mechanisms at vehicle level" guid="_dy0ooKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To ensure the effectiveness of the diagnostic coverage of the hardware fault detection, please refer to &quot;Table&#xD;
    17-&amp;nbsp;Effectiveness and failure coverage of safety mechanisms at vehicle level&quot; located at ISO 26262, volume 4, clause&#xD;
    8.4.4.3.4. this table covers&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Fault injection tests&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Error Guessing&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Tests derived from field experience&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    All these&amp;nbsp;techniques are recommended for ASILs A or B and highly recommended for ASILs C or D&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Fault injection introduces faults into the model at runtime to determine the how the software reacts. This is normally&#xD;
    achieved through a special test interface or hardware. This technique is often employed to improve test coverage of the&#xD;
    safety requirements, this because during normal operation safety mechanisms are not involved&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Error guessing employs expert knowledge and data collected from experience or the field. This is used to anticipate&#xD;
    possible errors in the test object.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Tests derived from field experience use the experience and data gathered from the field. Erroneous vehicle behavior or&#xD;
    newly discovered operational situations are analyzed and a set of tests is designed to check the vehicle with respect&#xD;
    to the new findings.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;justify&quot;>&#xD;
    For references to fault models see ISO 26262 volume 5: , Annex D, Table D.1&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br /></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_sFmxwKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw" name="Selection of  methods for the level of robustness" guid="_sFmxwKZpEeCmzNtTCfivQw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    To determine the test required to ensure the Level of robustness of the item, please refer to &quot;Table 18-Level of&#xD;
    robustness&quot; located in ISO 26262, volume 4, clause 8.4.4.3.5, in summary the tests to be carried out are&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Resource usage test&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Stress test&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Test for interference resistance and robustness under certain environmental condition&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;p>&#xD;
        Long term test&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
    &lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    All these&amp;nbsp;tests are recommended for ASIL B and highly recommended for ASILs C and D&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    At the item level lab cars or prototypes are usually employed to create&amp;nbsp;a dynamic environment for the tests. The&#xD;
    focus of these test are items such as power consumption or bus loading.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Stress tests are used to verify the correct operation of the item under high operational loads or extreme environmental&#xD;
    conditions.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A test for interference resistance and robustness under certain environmental conditions is a special case of stress&#xD;
    testing. This includes EMC and ESD tests.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Long term and user test under real life conditions, use a large sample size with normal users as testers. the users are&#xD;
    not bound to pre determined test scenarios, but the tests are carried out during normal real-life conditions.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    To describe the verification tools, methods and environment with pass and fail criteria to be applied at&#xD;
    the&amp;nbsp;vehicle integration level.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
